It looks like the new code does handle this explicitly and clears `page_type` to `UINT_MAX`, so it *should* work correctly. The check `page_has_type(page)` makes sure this is the case.

I reviewed the `mlx5` XDP patch and the changes to the `pp_page_to_nmdesc` macro. They seem to correctly use `PageNetpp` now. All the old `PP_MAGIC` checks are also correctly removed.

